   Department of Labor Historical Information

   The Departmental Historian is responsible for researching the history
   of the Department of Labor, providing information to the public,
   assisting those engaged in research related to the Department, and
   maintaining this Web site. The historical information on this site is
   in the public domain; attribution to the Department of Labor would be
   appreciated. For additional information and research assistance, please
   contact the Departmental Historian.

     Judson MacLaury
     Departmental Historian
     U.S. Department of Labor
     Room S-2312
     200 Constitution Ave. NW
     Washington, D.C. 20210

